dataCsv.Site_Description: The Tiller Wreck sits nearly intact on the bottom about two miles from the Port Dalhousie harbor entrance. The two-masted schooner Tiller Wreck is a local favorite dive site out of Port Dalhousie, ON in Lake Ontario. It is unidentified and nicknamed the Tiller Wreck due to the large tiller it ports. It has one mast and one large boom extant on site.
